                <div class="step-group">
                    <div class="step-group-title">üìÇ Data Migration</div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-checkbox" onclick="toggleStep(this)"></div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <div class="step-title">Migrate existing emails</div>
                            <div class="step-description">Move emails from current providers to Microsoft 365</div>
                            <details class="step-details">
                                <summary>Click for detailed step-by-step instructions</summary>
                                <div class="detailed-steps">
                                    <p><strong>For Gmail migration:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>In each Gmail account, enable IMAP:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Go to Gmail Settings ‚Üí Forwarding and POP/IMAP</li>
                                            <li>Enable IMAP access</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <li>Create app password for Gmail:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Go to Google Account settings</li>
                                            <li>Security ‚Üí 2-Step Verification ‚Üí App passwords</li>
                                            <li>Generate app password for "Mail"</li>
                                            <li>Save this password securely</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <li>In Microsoft 365 admin center:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Go to <strong>"Setup"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Data migration"</strong></li>
                                            <li>Choose <strong>"Gmail"</strong></li>
                                            <li>Click <strong>"Get started"</strong></li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <li>Add source Gmail account:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Email address: user's Gmail address</li>
                                            <li>Password: App password (not regular password)</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <li>Map to destination: <strong>user@kompas-nordic.com</strong></li>
                                        <li>Start migration and monitor progress</li>
                                        <li>Migration time: 2-8 hours depending on email volume</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>For Outlook.com migration:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Use Outlook desktop app migration:</li>
                                        <li>Add old account to Outlook desktop</li>
                                        <li>Add new Microsoft 365 account</li>
                                        <li>Select all emails from old account</li>
                                        <li>Drag and drop to new account folders</li>
                                        <li>Let sync complete (may take several hours)</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Verify migration success:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Check sent items are preserved</li>
                                        <li>Verify folder structure maintained</li>
                                        <li>Test search functionality</li>
                                        <li>Confirm calendar events migrated</li>
                                        <li>Check contacts are available</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <div class="warning-box">
                                        <strong>Important:</strong> Don't delete old email accounts until migration is verified and users are comfortable with new system
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </details>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-checkbox" onclick="toggleStep(this)"></div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <div class="step-title">Migrate files from on-premises server</div>
                            <div class="step-description">Move server files to SharePoint and OneDrive</div>
                            <details class="step-details">
                                <summary>Click for detailed step-by-step instructions</summary>
                                <div class="detailed-steps">
                                    <p><strong>Assess server data first:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Document all shared folders on server</li>
                                        <li>Note folder permissions and who has access</li>
                                        <li>Calculate total data size</li>
                                        <li>Identify large files (>100MB) that need special handling</li>
                                        <li>Check for any applications that depend on server files</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Use SharePoint Migration Tool:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Download SharePoint Migration Tool from Microsoft</li>
                                        <li>Install on a computer with access to server</li>
                                        <li>Launch tool and sign in with admin account</li>
                                        <li>Choose <strong>"File share"</strong> as source</li>
                                        <li>Enter server path: <code>\\servername\sharedfolder</code></li>
                                        <li>Enter credentials for server access</li>
                                        <li>Choose destination SharePoint site and library</li>
                                        <li>Map folders to SharePoint structure</li>
                                        <li>Start migration and monitor progress</li>
                                        <li>Review and fix any errors</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Manual migration for small amounts:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Open SharePoint site in browser</li>
                                        <li>Navigate to appropriate document library</li>
                                        <li>Drag and drop files/folders from server</li>
                                        <li>Wait for upload to complete</li>
                                        <li>Verify files are accessible</li>
                                        <li>Set appropriate permissions</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Set up OneDrive sync for users:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>On each user's computer, open OneDrive</li>
                                        <li>Sign in with new work account</li>
                                        <li>Choose folders to sync locally</li>
                                        <li>Move personal files to OneDrive folder</li>
                                        <li>Wait for sync to complete</li>
                                        <li>Verify files accessible from web and mobile</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <div class="info-box">
                                        <strong>Migration Strategy:</strong>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Company files ‚Üí SharePoint document libraries</li>
                                            <li>Individual user files ‚Üí OneDrive for Business</li>
                                            <li>Department files ‚Üí SharePoint department sites</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                    
                                    <div class="success-box">
                                        <strong>Success indicators:</strong>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>All critical files accessible in SharePoint</li>
                                            <li>Users can access files from any device</li>
                                            <li>Permissions work correctly</li>
                                            <li>Search finds documents quickly</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </details>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-checkbox" onclick="toggleStep(this)"></div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <div class="step-title">Migrate individual PC files</div>
                            <div class="step-description">Set up automatic backup of Desktop, Documents, Pictures</div>
                            <details class="step-details">
                                <summary>Click for detailed step-by-step instructions</summary>
                                <div class="detailed-steps">
                                    <p><strong>Set up Known Folder Move (automatic backup):</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>On each user's PC, open OneDrive</li>
                                        <li>Right-click OneDrive icon in system tray</li>
                                        <li>Click <strong>"Settings"</strong></li>
                                        <li>Go to <strong>"Backup"</strong> tab</li>
                                        <li>Click <strong>"Manage backup"</strong></li>
                                        <li>Select folders to back up:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Desktop ‚úì</li>
                                            <li>Documents ‚úì</li>
                                            <li>Pictures ‚úì</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <li>Click <strong>"Start backup"</strong></li>
                                        <li>Wait for initial sync (may take hours for large amounts)</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Alternative: Manual file copy:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Create folder structure in OneDrive</li>
                                        <li>Copy important files from:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Desktop</li>
                                            <li>Documents</li>
                                            <li>Pictures</li>
                                            <li>Downloads (if needed)</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <li>Paste into corresponding OneDrive folders</li>
                                        <li>Wait for sync to cloud</li>
                                        <li>Verify files accessible from web portal</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Handle large files and special cases:</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Files larger than 100GB:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Consider keeping on local storage</li>
                                            <li>Or use external storage solution</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <li>Software installers and license files:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Store in secure SharePoint library</li>
                                            <li>Restricted access only</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <li>Personal files mixed with work:</li>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Help user separate work vs personal</li>
                                            <li>Only work files go to OneDrive</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <div class="success-box">
                                        <strong>Result:</strong> Users' important files automatically backed up to cloud and accessible from anywhere
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </details>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step-group">
                    <div class="step-group-title">üë®‚Äçüè´ User Training</div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-checkbox" onclick="toggleStep(this)"></div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <div class="step-title">Conduct basic Microsoft 365 training (3 hours)</div>
                            <div class="step-description">Train users on essential functions</div>
                            <details class="step-details">
                                <summary>Click for detailed step-by-step instructions</summary>
                                <div class="detailed-steps">
                                    <p><strong>Session 1: Email and Basic Setup (1 hour)</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Help each user log in to office.com</li>
                                        <li>Show Outlook web interface</li>
                                        <li>Demonstrate sending and receiving emails</li>
                                        <li>Show shared mailboxes (info@, bookings@)</li>
                                        <li>Set up email signatures</li>
                                        <li>Show calendar and scheduling</li>
                                        <li>Set up mobile apps (Outlook, Teams)</li>
                                        <li>Test MFA and authenticator app</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Session 2: File Storage and Collaboration (1 hour)</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Show OneDrive personal storage</li>
                                        <li>Demonstrate file upload and sync</li>
                                        <li>Navigate SharePoint sites</li>
                                        <li>Practice sharing files with clients</li>
                                        <li>Show version history and recovery</li>
                                        <li>Mobile file access demonstration</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Session 3: Microsoft Teams and Communication (1 hour)</strong></p>
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Teams app overview</li>
                                        <li>Channel navigation and posting</li>
                                        <li>File sharing in Teams</li>
                                        <li>Video calling and meetings</li>
                                        <li>Meeting with external clients</li>
                                        <li>Mobile Teams usage</li>
                                    </ol>
                                    
                                    <p><strong>Create training materials:</strong></p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Quick reference cards (laminated)</li>
                                        <li>Step-by-step guides with screenshots</li>
                                        <li>Emergency contact information</li>
                                        <li>Common troubleshooting solutions</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    
                                    <div class="info-box">
                                        <strong>Training Tips:</strong>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Keep sessions short and practical</li>
                                            <li>Focus on daily tasks they'll actually use</li>
                                            <li>Have users practice on their own devices</li>
                                            <li>Record sessions for future reference</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </details>
                        </div>
                    </div>

